g.text: - A software development environment used to develop Java applications
- Provides all the necessary tools, libraries, and runtime environments required to build
What happens when we press the Run button in IDE?
- converts java source code into bytecode
- bytecode is executed by the Java Virtual Machine (JVM)
- Includes the JVM and the essential libraries to run java applications
- acts as the running part of java
- Executes the compiled java bytecode on various platforms
- provides platform independence (write once, run anywhere)
- Build automation: The IDE can automate tasks such as compiling code,
packaging software, running unit tests, and deploying applications.
- Interprets each instruction in Main.class one by one
- Translates into a platform specific operation and executes it
- Moves to the next bytecode instruction and repeats the process
